main event: A witness observed a flashing or blinking object low on the horizon while driving in Smyrna, Delaware on January 16, 1961.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 10 minutes,The object was observed through the front window of the car,The witness described the object as appearing like a star,The witness was driving at approximately 55 miles per hour when they noticed the object,The object was estimated to be 15 degrees from true North and 10 degrees above the horizon.
witness description: 31-year-old male, graduate of Annapolis and a veteran of the Navy
